==English==

===Etymology===
From French ''[[toilette]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔɪlɪt|-ɔɪlɪt]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A ceramic [[bowl]] that can be flushed down with water after disposing of human [[waste]] in it.
# A [[bathroom]], [[lavatory]] or [[water closet]] ([[w.c.]]): a room containing a '''toilet'''.
#''(figurative)'' A shabby or dirty place, especially, a lounge/bar/pub/tavern.
#:''Let’s get out of this toilet!''
# Personal grooming. 
#:'''1917''' ''"It is a quarter-past two," he said. "Your telegram was dispatched about one. But no one can glance at your toilet and attire without seeing that your disturbance dates from the moment of your waking."'' — Arthur Conan Doyle, ''[[s:The Adventure of Wisteria Lodge|"The Adventure of Wisteria Lodge"]].

